comment: Williams (NYK) legally contests Booker's (UTA) shot attempt. Booker initiates any incidental contact with his non-shooting arm.
Lopez (NYK) sets the screen on Booker (UTA) and gives him room to avoid the contact. The two players briefly engage and separate immediately after the screen.
Burke (UTA) and Williams (NYK) make incidental contact with one another while attempting to secure the rebound.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
Anthony (NYK) sets the screen on Johnson (UTA) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Hood (UTA) was behind the three point line on his shot attempt was confirmed.
Gobert (UTA) commits a take foul on Porzingis (NYK).
Anthony (NYK) grabs and holds Hayward (UTA) affecting his FOM during the inbounds play.
Afflalo (NYK) and Hood (UTA) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Porzingis (NYK) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Hayward (UTA) that affects his jump shot attempt.
Hayward (UTA) and Gobert (UTA) maintain legal guarding position as they contest Anthony's (NYK) driving shot attempt.
Lopez (NYK) makes incidental contact with Hayward (UTA) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Gobert (UTA) makes incidental contact with Lopez (NYK) who is off balance as he jumps for the rebound.
Hayward (UTA) moves his pivot foot after ending his dribble.
Anthony (NYK) grabs and holds Burke's (UTA) arm as he sets the screen, affecting his ability to defend.
Anthony (NYK) and Hayward (UTA) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Anthony (NYK) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Hayward's (UTA) drive and shot attempt. Any contact on the play is initiated by Hayward.
Hayward (UTA) makes contact with Anthony's (NYK) arm causing him to lose control of the ball after he secures the rebound.
Anthony (NYK) moves his pivot foot while trying to pass out of the double team. The official is looking for any illegal contact and does not pick up the pivot foot.
Hood (UTA) makes contact with Williams' (NYK) body on his layup attempt.
Lyles (UTA) makes incidental contact with Williams (NYK) during rebounding.
Lopez (NYK) makes contact with Lyles' (UTA) arm and body that affects his layup attempt.
Gobert (UTA) cleanly blocks Galloway's (NYK) driving layup attempt.
Lyles (UTA) makes incidental contact with Lopez' (NYK) non-shooting arm that does not affect his layup attempt.
Hayward (UTA) grabs Anthony's (NYK) arm while reaching in for the steal.
Lyles (UTA) and Burke (UTA) maintain legal guarding position as they trap Galloway (NYK) in the back court.
Lyles (UTA) and Lopez (NYK) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding. Lyles then cleanly knocks the ball away from Lopez.

After communicating with the Replay Center, there was no conclusive video evidence to overturn the call on the court that the ball was simultaneously touched by Lyles (UTA) and Lopez (NYK) prior to going OOB. The ruling on the court of a jump ball stood.
Gobert (UTA) commits a take foul on Williams (NYK).
Gobert (UTA) dislodges Lopez (NYK) affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Johnson (UTA) commits a take foul on Galloway (NYK).
